        optionFeedback: [`Klebsiella pneumoniae osteomyelitis is rare.`,`  Tuberculosis can cause osteomyelitis but it is not the most common cause in patients with sickle cell anemia. Presentation is usually chronic, not acute.`,`<!--Answers:-->This patient has acute pyogenic osteomyelitis. Although Staphylococcus aureus is the most common cause of acute pyogenic osteomyelitis, Salmonella osteomyelitis is more common in patients with sickle cell disease `,`Borrelia burgdorferi is the causative agent of Lyme arthritis, which is usually a migratory arthritis associated with involvement of skin and other organs. There is no association with sickle cell disease.`,`<!--E.-->Treponema pallidum is the causative agent of syphilis. While bone lesions may be seen in tertiary syphilis, this disease would be uncommon in the pediatric population and is not associated with sickle cell disease.`],
